<subSubSection id="8FAA1E8DFF01FF33FD49242BFF258F50" lastPageId="147" lastPageNumber="147" pageId="146" pageNumber="146" type="description">
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FF01FF33FD49242BFEDB8C7A" blockId="146.[670,1199,1505,1763]" lastBlockId="147.[128,657,905,1763]" lastPageId="147" lastPageNumber="147" pageId="146" pageNumber="146">
IDENTIFICATION: Eger (1977) provided species diagnoses and a key in her revision of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FF01FF32FCEC2466FCF78FB0" authorityName="G.S.Miller" authorityYear="1906" box="[798,892,1652,1675]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Eumops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="146" pageNumber="146" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF01FF32FCEC2466FCF78FB0" box="[798,892,1652,1675]" italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="146">Eumops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has not been superceded by any comparably comprehensive study. 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FF01FF32FD1D24BCFC138FFE" author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." box="[751,920,1710,1733]" journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="146" pageNumber="146" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Husson (1962</bibRefCitation>
, 1978) gave a detailed description and comparative measurements of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FF00FF33FF51219BFED48A9B" box="[163,351,905,928]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Eumops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="147" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auripendulus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FF51219BFF3E8A9B" box="[163,181,905,928]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FF34219BFED48A9B" box="[198,351,905,928]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">auripendulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Surinam, and additional information can be found in 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FF00FF33FDDD21B5FF468AE0" author="Sanborn, C. C." journalOrPublisher="J. Mammal." pageId="147" pageNumber="147" pagination="347 - 357" part="13" refId="ref99896" refString="Sanborn, C. C. 1932. The bats of the genus Eumops. J. Mammal. 13: 347 - 357." title="The bats of the genus Eumops" type="journal article" year="1932">Sanborn (1932)</bibRefCitation>
under the account for 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FF00FF33FDFB21D6FD1B8AE0" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[521,656,964,987]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="147" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="abrasus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FDFB21D6FD908AE0" box="[521,539,964,987]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FDC621D6FD1B8AE0" box="[564,656,964,987]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">abrasus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(now considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FF00FF33FDA421F0FF628D2C" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Eumops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="147" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auripendulus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FDA421F0FF628D2C" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">auripendulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; see Goodwin, 1960; 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FF00FF33FE1B21EDFD078D2D" author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." box="[489,652,1023,1046]" journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="147" pageNumber="147" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Husson, 1962</bibRefCitation>
, 1978; 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FF00FF33FF3F260FFEDB8D0F" author="Eger, J. L." bookContentInfo="8 pp." box="[205,336,1053,1076]" journalOrPublisher="Life Sci. Occas. Pap. R. Ontario Mus" pageId="147" pageNumber="147" refId="ref92826" refString="Eger, J. L. 1974. A new subspecies of the bat Eumops auripendulus (Chiroptera: Molossidae), from Argentina and eastern Brazil. Life Sci. Occas. Pap. R. Ontario Mus. 25: 8 pp." title="A new subspecies of the bat Eumops auripendulus (Chiroptera: Molossidae), from Argentina and eastern Brazil" type="book" year="1974">Eger, 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 1977). Two subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FF00FF33FF722629FECC8D69" box="[128,327,1083,1106]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Eumops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="147" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auripendulus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FF722629FF198D69" box="[128,146,1083,1106]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FF5C2629FECC8D69" box="[174,327,1083,1106]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">auripendulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are currently recognized with the following continental distributions (
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FF00FF33FF7A2664FE9B8DB6" author="Eger, J. L." bookContentInfo="8 pp." box="[136,272,1142,1165]" journalOrPublisher="Life Sci. Occas. Pap. R. Ontario Mus" pageId="147" pageNumber="147" refId="ref92826" refString="Eger, J. L. 1974. A new subspecies of the bat Eumops auripendulus (Chiroptera: Molossidae), from Argentina and eastern Brazil. Life Sci. Occas. Pap. R. Ontario Mus. 25: 8 pp." title="A new subspecies of the bat Eumops auripendulus (Chiroptera: Molossidae), from Argentina and eastern Brazil" type="book" year="1974">Eger, 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 1977; Koopman, 1994): 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FDA12665FDEE8DB5" box="[595,613,1143,1166]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FD882665FD028DB5" box="[634,649,1143,1166]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">a</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FF00FF33FF722686FE928D90" box="[128,281,1172,1195]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Eumops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="147" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auripendulus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FF722686FE928D90" box="[128,281,1172,1195]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">auripendulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(southern Mexico to Amazonia, including the Guianas) and 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FDF426A0FD938DF2" box="[518,536,1202,1225]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FDD826A0FDB28DF2" box="[554,569,1202,1225]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">a</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FF00FF33FDB926A0FD1B8DF2" box="[587,656,1202,1225]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="147" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FDB926A0FD1B8DF2" box="[587,656,1202,1225]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(northern Argentina, southern Paraguay, and eastern Brazil). These taxa are distinguished on the basis of size, with 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FF00FF33FE3E271EFD9A8C18" box="[460,529,1292,1315]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="147" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FE3E271EFD9A8C18" box="[460,529,1292,1315]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being the larger of the two.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FF00FF33FF6F2755FF258F50" blockId="147.[128,657,905,1763]" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">
Our voucher material conforms in all respects to Eger’s (1977) description of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FF00FF33FD942774FD8C8CA1" authority="auripendulus" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Eumops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="147" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="auripendulus" subSpecies="auripendulus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FD942774FD8C8CA1" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">Eumops auripendulus auripendulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The Paracou specimens are also comparable in size to those reported from Surinam by 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FF00FF33FDCB27ADFF4C8CCF" author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="147" pageNumber="147" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Husson (1962</bibRefCitation>
, 1978), although one of our females has a shorter maxillary toothrow and narrow­ er skull than either of the females whose measurements he published (op. cit.: table 32).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8FAA1E8DFF00FF33FF6F2460FD058FD8" pageId="147" pageNumber="147" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FF00FF33FF6F2460FD058FD8" blockId="147.[128,657,905,1763]" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">
FIELD OBSERVATIONS: Our three specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FF00FF33FF502482FE288F9C" box="[162,419,1680,1703]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Eumops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="147" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auripendulus">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FF00FF33FF502482FE288F9C" box="[162,419,1680,1703]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="147">Eumops auripendulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Paracou were captured in mistnets suspended 17­­23 m above a narrow dirt road through the forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
